import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['ret'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['ret'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['ret'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily returns?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['open'], data['close'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Open Price')
    ax.set_ylabel('Close Price')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between open and close prices?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['close'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Close Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of the stock price over time?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data['high'], data['low']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['High', 'Low'])
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between high and low prices?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
